Introduced and read first time: February 4, 2026
Assigned to: Education, Energy, and the Environment
Committee Report: Favorable
Senate action: Adopted
Read second time: March 2, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 County Boards of Library Trustees – Membership – Student Member
3 FOR the purpose of authorizing a county board of library trustees to provide for the
4 selection of a student member of the board; establishing the qualifications, term of
5 office, and voting rights of the student member of a county board of library trustees,
6 if selected; and generally relating to the membership of county boards of library
7 trustees.
8 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
9 Article – Education
10 Section 23–403 and 23–404
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
13 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
14 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
15 Article – Education
16 23–403.
17 (a) (1) Except as provided in paragraph (3) of this subsection AND
18 SUBSECTION (G) OF THIS SECTION, each board of library trustees consists of seven
19 APPOINTED members appointed by the county governing body from nominees submitted
20 by the board of library trustees.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *sb0535*

2 SENATE BILL 535
1 (2) A board that existed before 1945 under a corporate charter may
2 continue as constituted if:
3 (i) It has at least seven APPOINTED members;
4 (ii) The APPOINTED members are chosen on the basis of character,
5 ability, and demonstrated interest in library matters; and
6 (iii) The APPOINTED members meet the qualifications required
7 under subsection (b) of this section.
8 (3) In Harford County, the Board of Trustees consists of at least 7
9 APPOINTED members, but not more than 11 APPOINTED members, appointed by the
10 county governing body from nominees submitted by the Board of Trustees.
11 (b) The APPOINTED members of the board shall be:
12 (1) Representative of the area the library serves; and
13 (2) Residents of the county that the library serves.
14 (c) (1) (I) Except as provided in subsections (d) and (e) of this section, [a]
15 AN APPOINTED member of a board serves for a term of 5 years and until a successor is
16 appointed and qualifies.
17 (II) [These] THE terms OF THE APPOINTED MEMBERS are
18 staggered as required by the terms of the APPOINTED members serving on the board as of
19 July 1, 1978.
20 (2) Except as provided in paragraph (4) of this subsection, [a] AN
21 APPOINTED member may be reappointed but may not serve more than two consecutive
22 terms.
23 (3) [A] AN APPOINTED member appointed to fill a vacancy in an
24 unexpired term:
25 (i) Serves only for the remainder of that term and until a successor
26 is appointed and qualifies; and
27 (ii) Is eligible for appointment to serve two additional consecutive
28 terms.
29 (4) [A] AN APPOINTED member of the Board of the Prince George’s
30 County Memorial Library System may serve an unlimited number of consecutive terms of
31 office.

SENATE BILL 535 3
1 (d) In Charles County, [a] AN APPOINTED member of the Board serves for a term
2 of 4 years.
3 (e) In Harford County, [a] AN APPOINTED member of the Board serves for a term
4 of 5 years, beginning on July 1, and until a successor is appointed and qualifies.
5 (f) Each member of a board serves without compensation.
6 (G) (1) A BOARD MAY PROVIDE FOR THE SELECTION OF A STUDENT
7 MEMBER OF THE BOARD IN ACCORDANCE WITH THIS SUBSECTION.
8 (2) A STUDENT MEMBER SHALL BE SELECTED BY A PROCESS
9 ESTABLISHED BY THE BOARD.
10 (3) THE STUDENT MEMBER OF A BOARD SHALL:
11 (I) BE A JUNIOR OR SENIOR YEAR STUDENT ENROLLED IN A
12 PUBLIC OR NONPUBLIC HIGH SCHOOL IN THE COUNTY THAT THE LIBRARY SERVES,
13 WHO IS OF GOOD CHARACTER AND IS IN GOOD STANDING IN THE STUDENT’S HIGH
14 SCHOOL;
15 (II) BE SELECTED IN THE STUDENT’S SOPHOMORE OR JUNIOR
16 YEAR BY A METHOD ESTABLISHED BY THE BOARD;
17 (III) HAVE AN INTEREST IN LIBRARY MATTERS; AND
18 (IV) SERVE A TERM OF 1 YEAR.
19 (4) A STUDENT MEMBER SELECTED TO FILL A VACANCY IN AN
20 UNEXPIRED TERM:
21 (I) SERVES ONLY FOR THE REMAINDER OF THAT TERM AND
22 UNTIL A SUCCESSOR IS SELECTED AND QUALIFIES; AND
23 (II) IS ELIGIBLE FOR SELECTION FOR A FULL TERM IF THE
24 STUDENT MEETS THE ELIGIBILITY REQUIREMENTS UNDER PARAGRAPH (3) OF THIS
25 SUBSECTION.
26 (5) (I) SUBJECT TO SUBPARAGRAPH (II) OF THIS PARAGRAPH, A
27 STUDENT MEMBER OF A BOARD MAY VOTE ON ALL POLICY MATTERS BEFORE THE
28 BOARD.

4 SENATE BILL 535
1 (II) A BOARD MAY ADOPT A POLICY OR BYLAW TO AUTHORIZE A
2 STUDENT MEMBER TO VOTE ON ADDITIONAL NONPOLICY MATTERS BEFORE THE
3 BOARD.
4 23–404.
5 (a) Each year, each board of library trustees:
6 (1) Shall elect one of its APPOINTED members as its [chairman] CHAIR;
7 and
8 (2) May elect any other officer it requires FROM AMONG THE APPOINTED
9 MEMBERS OF THE BOARD.
10 (b) The treasurer of each board of library trustees shall be bonded adequately.
11 (c) Each board of library trustees may determine the time and place of its
12 meetings and may adopt rules for the conduct of its meetings. However:
13 (1) Each board shall meet at least once every 3 months;
14 (2) Any final action of a board shall be taken at a public meeting; and
15 (3) The minutes of board meetings shall be open to the public.
16 (d) (1) Any member of a board of library trustees who fails to attend at least
17 half of the scheduled meetings of the board during any calendar year shall be considered to
18 have resigned from the board.
19 (2) The [chairman] CHAIR of the board of library trustees shall report the
20 member’s name and nonattendance to the county governing body by January 15 of the
21 following year.
22 (3) The county governing body may reject the resignation if the member
23 explains his nonattendance satisfactorily.
24 (4) The resignation is effective from the date of the final review by the
25 county governing body, which shall be within 10 days after it receives the report from the
26 [chairman] CHAIR of the board of library trustees. The county governing body shall fill any
27 resulting vacancy as provided in § 23–403 of this subtitle.
28 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
29 1, 2026.

